  "body": "## Simple Summary\r\nAdd `SafeERC20` interface, that allows working with non-standard ERC20 tokens\r\n\r\n## Motivation\r\nWhen working with ERC20s, there are sometimes non-compliant implementations that are hard to work with. Adding an internal implementation that is a drop-in replacement for the normal `ERC20` interface, but uses the \"Safe\" versions of these calls for common variants would help users who want access to this functionality without having to code it themselves. This is common enough functionality that it should be supported.\r\n\r\n## Specification\r\nThe new interface type `SafeERC20` is basically a `ERC20` interface, except it performs non-standard calls for `ERC20.transfer()` and `ERC20.transferFrom()` in order to handle different common scenarios. [OpenZeppelin](https://github.com/openzeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/master/contracts/token/ERC20/SafeERC20.sol) has an implementation of this very library in common use in the ecosystem, with a Vyper-esque variant here:\r\nhttps://ethereum.stackexchange.com/questions/84775/is-there-a-vyper-equivalent-to-openzeppelins-safeerc20-safetransfer/84776\r\n\r\nNote that this \"interface\" can NOT be used with `implements`, and is only an option for those who need it (there will be some increased gas usage)\r\n\r\n## Backwards Compatibility\r\nFully backwards compatible.\r\n\r\n## Dependencies\r\nNo dependencies\r\n\r\n## References\r\nhttps://github.com/openzeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/master/contracts/token/ERC20/SafeERC20.sol\r\nhttps://ethereum.stackexchange.com/questions/84775/is-there-a-vyper-equivalent-to-openzeppelins-safeerc20-safetransfer/84776\r\n\r\n\r\n## Copyright\r\nCopyright and related rights waived via [CC0](https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/)\r\n",
